            "answer_text": "Blue refers to the clear blue sky. Normally a thunderstorm does not happen when the sky is clear blue. When it happens, that surprises us since it is unexpected. This explains the \u2018connection\u2019 to \u201cblue\u201d in the idiom. According to some English scholars the idiom is a derivation of an old idiom \"a bolt out of the blue\" or \u201ca bolt from the blue\u201d which refers to a completely unexpected and surprising act, like a thunderbolt from a clear blue sky. ",
